commText: Jaiswal and Kohler-Cadmore are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, no run, angled across the left hander, Jaiswal waits and dabs it late to short third
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, no run, I0$ good length ball around off, not quite there for the drive and hence Jaiswal mistimes it to cover
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, 1 run, back of a length close to off, Jaiswal gets on top of the bounce and directs it to the vacant backward point region

Bhuvneshwar to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, uhhh! Nearly played it on. Kohler-Cadmore walks down to counter the swing and the length is shortened, the ball still swings in and takes the inside edge, bounces over the stumps
Klaasen comes up to the stumps
Bhuvneshwar to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, I0$ fraction short and outside off, Kohler-Cadmore slashes it to deep backward point
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, SIX, poor delivery to end the over and Bhuvi is made to pay. I0$ leg-lined delivery and Jaiswal helps it along the way, swings it hard and sends it sailing over long leg
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, I0$ full pitcher on middle, Kohler-Cadmore drives it towards mid-off and is denied a boundary by a diving Markram, he gets across and dives full length to keep it to a single
Slip for Cummins as well
Cummins to Jaiswal, 1 run, back of a length on off, Jaiswal is cramped but manages to knock it towards point

Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, 2 runs, I0$ back of a length delivery, Kohler-Cadmore heaves across the line and gets it high on the bat, clears the infield and Shabaz hunts it down from mid-wicket, just a brace
Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, I0$ short of length on off, stopped a bit and Kohler-Cadmore checked his block to the off-side

Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, appeal for a caught behind. Umpire Virender Sharma is not convinced. Very full delivery around off, Kohler-Cadmore makes room and looks to squeeze the drive, misses and the bat brushes the ground

Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, in the air and short. Kohler-Cadmore backs away and Cummins follows him, cramps him with a back of a length delivery and Kohler-Cadmore pushes it uppishly towards mid-wicket, Shahbaz dives but the ball evades him
Bhuvneshwar to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, now Kohler-Cadmore advances while making room, Bhuvi cramps him as well and the inside edge rolls back to Klaasen

Bhuvneshwar to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, I0$ on a length and outside off, Kohler-Cadmore stays rooted to the crease and has a slash. Misses and is beaten on the outside edge. Jaiswal walks up and has a word
Bhuvneshwar to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, I0$ full pitcher around off, Kohler-Cadmore pushes it to mid-off and quickly crosses over

Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, FOUR, I0$ back of a length delivery and Jaiswal is quick to pick the length, he transfers his weight back and pulls it in front of square, splitting mid-wicket and mid-on perfectly
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, 1 run, short of length delivery on off, Jaiswal opens the bat face and directs it square on the off-side

Bhuvneshwar to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, angled in and Kohler-Cadmore is cramped up, he has a heave across the line and is struck on the thigh pad. He's really struggling and needs to get Jaiswal on strike as much as possible
Cummins to Jaiswal, 1 run, short of length delivery at the body, Jaiswal pulls to deep square leg
There is a delay in play not sure why. Umpire Menon has a word with Klaasen and then with the batters, probably conveying what the hold up is. They are ready to continue now
Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, he's missing out on full tosses now. This was an attempted yorker which Cummins got wrong, Kohler-Cadmore slices the drive straight to cover-point
Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, short of length delivery and no room on offer, Kohler-Cadmore knocks it to point and wants a single, Jaiswal sends him back

Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, FOUR, will that free him up? Short of length delivery and there was room on offer this time, Kohler-Cadmore opens the bat face and ramps it over short third, the ball hits the cushions on the half volley
Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, bouncer at the batter, Kohler-Cadmore backs away and watches the ball sail over him

The DRS is not available right now and that was the stoppage early in the over as the third umpire relayed that message to the onfield umpires. The previous delivery looked high but RR can't review as DRS is down
Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Kohler-Cadmore, out Caught by Tripathi!! That ends Kohler-Cadmore's struggles. Rajasthan Royals might not mind that. He was stuck at one end and was not able to get the ball off the square, tries to whack this out of the ground and skies it off the outer half over the cover-point region, Tripathi runs back and takes a good catch. Kohler-Cadmore c Tripathi b Cummins 10(16) [4s-1]
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Jaiswal, leg byes, 1 run, back of a length and nips in, Jaiswal is caught in the crease and beaten on the inside edge, struck high on the back pad and the ball rolls to backward point
DRS is available now
T Natarajan to Samson, no run, back of a length close to off, Samson arches back and knocks it to cover
T Natarajan to Samson, 2 runs, fullish delivery around off, Samson eases the drive straight of mid-off but Markram from mid-on gives chase and hauls it in just before the rope, saved a couple
T Natarajan to Samson, no run, I0$ back of a length on off, Samson opens the bat face and angles it to cover-point
T Natarajan to Samson, no run, I0$ back of a length on off, Samson punches it firmly to cover-point
T Natarajan to Samson, wide, bouncer but too short and too high, Samson does not even duck to evade it
T Natarajan to Samson, FOUR, extra ball costs Natarajan a boundary. I0$ short and wide outside off, Samson cracks the cut in front of square and beats the deep point near the rope
Highlights (1-5 overs) - Jaiswal's six off the final ball spoils Bhuvi's over - Cummins bowls a tight over - Boundary for Jaiswal; TKC off to a scratchy start - Cummins nips out TKC
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [2.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack

Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, SIX, Jaiswal has fancied Bhuvi tonight. That's his second six off the pacer. Fraction short and Jaiswal backed away, gave himself the space to free his hands and pumps it over long-on

Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, FOUR, RR need a big over to end the powerplay and Jaiswal has started nicely. Full delivery on leg-stump, right in the slot and Jaiswal thumps it straight down the ground. He does not bother to run..

Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, no run, moves away and Bhuvi goes full at the stumps, driven firmly to mid-off and Cummins fumbles, but no risky single taken. Jaiswal wanted the run but Samson quckly sends him back

Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, FOUR, slower ball and Jaiswal has no problems dealing with it, knuckle ball outside off, Jaiswal waits and drives on the rise through extra cover, giving Cummins no chance near mid-off

Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, FOUR, this is excellent batting. Short of length and it was off-pace, Jaiswal rides the bounce and opens the bat face as he plays the punch, places it behind square and beats a diving backward point
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, 1 run, I0$ slower ball on leg-stump, Jaiswal swipes it to deep square leg and retains strike

Timeout! That 19-run over to end the powerplay evens out the first six overs. SRH came out with a plan and stuck to it until Bhuvi was taken apart by Jaiswal. TKC struggled and Cummins sent him packing. But the two Indian batters in the middle and the one to come next are the ones in form and SRH will know that.
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Unadkat to Jaiswal, no run, short of length outside off, stops on Jaiswal a tad, he punches and it's off the thick outside half, was in the air but well wide of Unadkat, to his right
Unadkat to Jaiswal, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Jaiswal gets forward to drive to long-on
Unadkat round the wicket.
Unadkat to Samson, 1 run, short of length and a hint of shape away from off-stump, Samson guides with an open face to third man
Unadkat to Jaiswal, wide, slower ball off-cutter dug in outside off, Jaiswal slashes and misses, too high and it's a wide
Unadkat to Jaiswal, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Jaiswal punches to long-on
Unadkat to Samson, no run, slower ball off-cutter dug in short, Samson tries to help the pull, soft edge and it does not carry to Klaasen, well short in fact
Unadkat to Samson, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full on the stumps, Samson eases a single to long-on
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Samson, 1 run, good length and drifts into leg-stump, turned through the vacant mid-wicket area

Shahbaz Ahmed to Jaiswal, SIX, Jaiswal does the audacious. But after playing the reverse-sweep he grabs the right hammy. A grimace too. Nails the reverse-sweep from leg and middle, all the way over deep backward point
Shahbaz Ahmed to Jaiswal, 1 run, fullish on leg-stump, Jaiswal gets forward to drive to long-on
Shahbaz Ahmed to Samson, 1 run, tossed up full on the stumps, Samson gets forward to drive to long-off
Shahbaz Ahmed to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shahbaz Ahmed to Jaiswal, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! Jaiswal has thrown it away. Does this way too often. Cannot control himself as he sees the left-arm spinner, comes down the track and tries to loft big, horrible miscue as he is not to the pitch, easy catch for long-off and Samad is not dropping that. Near the boundary cushions, Jaiswal waves the bat at thin air in frustration. Is that the opening SRH need? Jaiswal c Abdul Samad b Shahbaz Ahmed 42(21) [4s-4 6s-3]
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, Riyan Parag gets forward to drive to long-off
Abhishek Sharma, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Abhishek Sharma to Riyan Parag, no run, ooh! Hint of turn on middle and off, Riyan Parag on the forward defence gets a soft outside-edge to short third man
Abhishek Sharma to Riyan Parag, 1 run, again holds on the pitch, good length and Riyan Parag knocks it wide of cover
Abhishek Sharma to Samson, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Abhishek Sharma to Samson, out Caught by Markram!! What a good bowling change this is! SRH are thrilled to bits. Samson head down walks back. A flat length delivery on the stumps, Samson goes on the back foot to pull and does not place it wide of long-on, Markram is one of the safest around and he goes to his right to take it easily. Never looked like dropping that. Abhishek Sharma is warmly hugged by Cummins. Samson c Markram b Abhishek Sharma 10(11) [4s-1]
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, flat back of a length outside off, cut wide of backward point and the fielder there dives to his right and keeps it to one
Yashasvi Jaiswal vs Spin in IPL 2024 Runs: 101 Balls: 59 Dismissals: 1 (today) SR: 172.2
Abhishek Sharma to Riyan Parag, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, pushed wide of cover
Sanju Samson vs spin in IPL 2024 Runs: 181 Balls: 130 Dismissals: 2 SR: 139.2
A slip in now.
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, flat back of a length outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Dhruv Jurel, no run, tossed up full outside off, neat forward defence
Shahbaz Ahmed to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, full on leg-stump, flicked to deep backward square leg
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, no run, flat length delivery on the stumps, pushed to cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, no run, good length outside off, punched to cover, two dots
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, no run, good length and tight on the stumps, defended in front of backward point and Dhruv Jurel sends Riyan Parag back
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, tossed up full outside off, wristy and powerful drive wide of cover but sweeper cover gets across and cuts it off to his right

Highlights (6-10 overs) - 41 runs | 2 wickets - Bhuvi to Jaiswal: 6 4 0 4 4 1 - Unadkat varies his pace well in his 1st over - Shahbaz removes Jaiswal after conceding a six in the over - Samson falls to Abhishek Sharma - The asking rate goes above 10 RPO
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, good length and quicker on leg-stump, nudged to deep mid-wicket
Abhishek Sharma to Riyan Parag, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, pushed to long-on
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, Tripathi now at deep backward square leg does well as he runs and dives to his right to keep it to two, was down leg, swiped hard and was heading to the fence
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, back of a length outside off, cut wide of sweeper cover and Shahbaz at sweeper cover slides to his left to keep it to two
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, no run, fullish outside off, pushed to backward point
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, no run, fraction short outside off, but extra bounce, Dhruv Jurel cuts to backward point and another dot
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! Sangakkara in the RR dugout looks shell-shocked. Sunny Gavaskar on air asks "seriously" thrice as he laments the lack of temperament in Riyan Parag. Was not for that ambitious shot. A flat back of a length delivery on off, extra bounce, he sinks low and tries to swipe, thick top-edge goes straight up and Abhishek at deep mid-wicket takes it nonchalantly. The impact player doing it for SRH. Now RR have a mountain to climb. Riyan Parag c Abhishek Sharma b Shahbaz Ahmed 6(10)
Ravichandran Ashwin, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Shahbaz Ahmed to Ashwin, no run, look at that turn! Nicely tossed up outside off, lots of revs, turns a mile and beats Ashwin's drive, Klaasen has the bails off but Ashwin had gone nowhere

Shahbaz Ahmed to Ashwin, no run, again turn and this pitch now looks like it will help the spinners. Quicker and fuller outside off, Ashwin's feet go nowhere and he is beaten on the drive. Ashwin has a suspicious look at the pitch
Shahbaz Ahmed to Ashwin, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shahbaz Ahmed to Ashwin, out Caught by Klaasen!! Two in the over and Shahbaz Ahmed is jumping for joy as he punches the air. Quicker length delivery outside off, turns a tad, extra bounce, Ashwin cuts and the thick top-edge is superbly held by Klaasen. Not an easy catch but he had the gloves right in position and held it so nicely. SRH all over RR now. Ashwin c Klaasen b Shahbaz Ahmed 0(3)
Shimron Hetmyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Shahbaz Ahmed to Hetmyer, no run, full on off, pushed back
Shahbaz Ahmed to Hetmyer, 1 run, full on the pads, flicked through vacant mid-wicket and that's just 1 and 2 wickets off the over
Riyan Parag vs spin in IPL 2024 Runs: 197 Balls: 154 Dismissals: 2 Avg: 98.5 SR: 127.9
Aiden Markram, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Markram to Hetmyer, no run, full on the stumps, drilled straight to the fielder at extra-cover

Markram to Hetmyer, no ball, what was that? Markram has delivered the ball to short fine-leg. Must surely have slipped out. KP on air calls it the worst ball he has ever seen in cricket. Now a free-hit for Hetmyer. That looped well wide of Hetmyer and was nowhere near the cutstrip

Markram to Hetmyer, no run, that is such a poor review. RR and Hetmyer waste one. This is tossed up full outside off, turns and Hetmyer standing on leg-stump and even outside the leg-stump, tries to loft inside-out, misses, well inside the tramline
Markram to Hetmyer, 1 run, flat length delivery outside off, Hetmyer punches to sweeper cover
Markram to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, good length on off and middle, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Markram to Hetmyer, 1 run, full on the stumps, Hetmyer gets forward to push, thick inside-edge goes through the vacant mid-wicket area

Markram to Dhruv Jurel, SIX, a boundary after 34 balls. Dhruv Jurel hits this so well, comes down the track and gets to the pitch, goes with the turn and lofts nicely over deep mid-wicket. RR needed that hit
Abhishek Sharma [2.0-0-10-1] is back into the attack

Abhishek Sharma to Hetmyer, no run, how has Hetmyer missed that? A loopy juicy low full-toss and down leg, Hetmyer swings and misses, hits the pad but the impact is well outside the leg-stump, Hetmyer is disappointed as he is on his haunches

Abhishek Sharma to Hetmyer, 1 run, now Hetmyer is disappointed at Dhruv Jurel after the Indian refuses the 2nd. Full on leg-stump, tucked to deep mid-wicket and Hetmyer tells Jurel that it was his call
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, flat length delivery on off, Dhruv Jurel pulls to deep mid-wicket
Abhishek Sharma to Hetmyer, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Abhishek Sharma to Hetmyer, out Bowled!! Hetmyer is gone and that's almost the game for RR. Jaiswal shakes his head on the dugout. A flat length delivery on off-stump, Hetmyer goes on the back foot to punch and misses, that is poor batting, he is standing on leg-stump and tried to force that and missed. Nothing special about that delivery, just flat and quick. Hetmyer b Abhishek Sharma 4(10)
Rovman Powell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Abhishek Sharma to Powell, no run, flat length delivery outside off, Powell sees till the end and then lets it go, was thinking about a cut for a moment
Abhishek Sharma to Powell, 1 run, length delivery outside off, Powell defends with soft hands wide of slip and takes the run
STAT: 4 wickets is most for SRH spinners in an innings this season, bettering 3/94(5 overs) against DC in Delhi.
Timeout! RR have slipped badly to spin and this game looks beyond them now, unless Powell and Dhruv Jurel pull off something special.
Shahbaz Ahmed [3.0-0-14-3] is back into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Powell, no run, good length on off, Powell goes on the back foot to push to cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Powell, no run, flat good length outside off, dabbed straight to the fielder at backward point
Shahbaz Ahmed to Powell, no run, slower and good length outside off, nudged to the right of Shahbaz Ahmed who gets across and cuts it off
Hetmyer vs spin in IPL 2024 Inns: 3 Runs: 8 Balls: 17 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 2.66 SR: 47.05
Shahbaz Ahmed to Powell, 1 run, flat and back of a length outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, tossed up full on leg-stump, Dhruv Jurel turns around and reverse-sweeps it over backward point, no chance for sweeper cover as it runs away
Shahbaz Ahmed to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, superb hit. Full on the stumps, Dhruv Jurel makes room and thumps the inside-out drive, wide of both extra-cover and sweeper cover, terrific batting

Highlights (11-15 overs) - 29 runs | 3 wickets - Shahbaz removes Parag & Ashwin in the same over - Jurel hits a six vs Markram, a boundary after 34 balls - Abhishek cleans up Hetmyer  - Back-to-back fours for Jurel - Shahbaz's bowling figures: 4-0-23-3
Abhishek Sharma to Powell, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, no run, tossed up full outside off, pushed to cover
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, lots of flight outside off, too full and Dhruv Jurel has crashed this drive hard and wide of extra-cover. All along the ground too
Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, full on the stumps, driven through mid-wicket

Abhishek Sharma to Powell, 1 run, sloppy from SRH. Was slower and wider outside off, Powell drives to backward point and he is sent back, the throw is well wide of Klaasen and Powell did not know where the ball was, he was fully focussed on placing his bat inside the crease, then Dhruv Jurel had to scream at him to catch his attention, eventually the deep mid-wicket fielder is caught napping, he takes it easy and they cross over, deep mid-wicket did not attack the throw at all

Abhishek Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, again tossed up and too full, outside off, Dhruv Jurel holds his shape and belts the drive straight down the ground, no chance again for either long-off or long-on. Dhruv Jurel is playing a fine knock
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-10-1] is back into the attack
Cummins to Powell, 1 run, slower short ball, the off-cutter dug in, Powell pulls to deep square leg

Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, SIX, near-terrific effort from Tripathi at deep square leg. He leaps but his right leg touches the cushion when the ball is in his hand. So will be six. Full and seam-up on the stumps, flicked nonchalantly and Tripathi nearly saved 5 as he palmed it back
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, no run, slower short ball down leg, off-cutter and Dhruv Jurel pulls and misses, did he get something on it? Not called a wide
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, again slower off-cutter dug in on the stumps, Dhruv Jurel pulls to deep mid-wicket
Cummins to Powell, 1 run, just off-cutters dug in and slower on the stumps, Powell pulls to deep square leg
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, tapped to deep mid-wicket as Dhruv Jurel retains the strike with that run
T Natarajan [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack

T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, no run, that has hit Dhruv Jurel on the throat! He is down immediately. A few SRH players check on him. Is through the pull early to this slower short ball, misses, the ball hits below the chin and rams into the throat
Shahbaz Ahmed bowling in Chennai in IPL 0/14(1) vs MI, 2021 (1st inns) 3/7(2) vs SRH, 2021 (2nd inns) 0/33(3) vs CSK, 2024 (1st inns) 3/23(4) vs RR, 2024 (2nd inns)*
The RR physio is out. A break in play.
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, full seam-up outside off, Dhruv Jurel drills it past the left-hand of T Natarajan who took it off as it was hit with force, but just a single to long-on
T Natarajan to Powell, no run, slower ball off-cutter dug in outside off, Powell pulls and misses
DYK? 9 overs is most for SRH spinners in an innings this season, bettering 8 overs against GT in Ahmedabad.
T Natarajan to Powell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Powell, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! Well-caught as Powell shakes his head on the way back. Abhishek misjudged the flight initially at deep mid-wicket but adjusted and took it neatly to his left. Another slower off-cutter dug in outside off, Powell does not get the elevation on the pull and he has to go. SRH inch closer. Powell c Abhishek Sharma b T Natarajan 6(12)
Trent Boult, right handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan to Boult, no run, full and seam-up on the stumps, drilled straight to the fielder at mid-off
T Natarajan to Boult, no run, slower and short off-cutter across Boult who swings and misses. Just one run and a wicket off that over
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, Dhruv Jurel keeps fighting. A slower short ball on the stumps, Dhruv Jurel pulls hard and wide of deep backward square leg
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, now to the left of deep square leg. 50 for Dhruv Jurel. Excellent knock this. Another slower off-cutter outside off, Dhruv Jurel pulls and beats the fielder
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, no run, does not take the run. A slower off-cutter dug in outside off, pulled straight to the fielder at deep mid-wicket
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, no run, slower off-cutter dug in on the stumps, Dhruv Jurel pulls to deep backward square leg and does not take the run again
Dhruv Jurel reviews for a non-wide. Above head-height, so a wide.
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, wide, the slower short ball goes over the head of Dhruv Jurel even though he was crouching slightly, he reviews and the third ump calls it a wide
A little girl in a RR jersey is in tears. That's what this game can do to you.
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, slower short ball down leg, Dhruv Jurel pulls to fine-leg and now takes one
Cummins to Boult, no run, slower off-cutter on a short of length on the stumps, Boult mistimes the pull to mid-wicket
SRH camp know the game is done barring a major miracle. Kavya Maran goes and hugs her dad as their celebrations begin. The last over and 42 needed.
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, no run, yorker length on off, driven to long-on and toe-ended, Dhruv Jurel does not take the run
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, low full-toss on off and middle, flicked away and wide of deep mid-wicket for four
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, no run, slower off-cutter dug in outside off, Dhruv Jurel nearly guides it to backward point, just short of Tripathi
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, no run, yorker length on the stumps, driven to long-on after a little shuffle across the stumps
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, no run, pacy short ball at Dhruv Jurel, hurries him on the pull, miscued and well short of fine-leg running in

T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, SRH into the final! A slower off-cutter dug in outside off, Dhruv Jurel pulls and it's off the toe-end, on to the body and in front of backward point, Dhruv Jurel calls Boult through even though the New Zealander wasn't that interested. SRH win by 36

23:19 Local Time, 17:49 GMT, 23:19 IST: Professional bowling and fielding performance sees SRH into the final. Jaiswal at the top threatened but his partner TKC struggled and fell. The key wickets were that of the top-order and help came from an unexpected source for SRH - their spinners. This season they have rarely used spin except for one or two games. But it's spin that won them the game tonight. The unlikely pairing of Shahbaz and Abhishek the two left-arm spinners ripped through the heart of RR's batting and that made it easy for the pacers. Shahbaz the hero with a three-fer including two in one over and he got the big wickets of Jaiswal and Parag. Abhishek took care of Samson and Hetmyer and that middle-overs slump never allowed RR to get back. The pitch got progressively slower and strokemaking became difficult. Tremendous captaincy from Cummins who realised that spin was the way to go and threw the ball to his tweakers. Also no dew played a huge part as the ball gripped and turned. Only Dhruv Jurel kept fighting and ended up with a good knock. In the end an easy win for SRH and it sets up a rematch of Qualifier 1 on Sunday (26th) for the final. Stay tuned for the presentations...

Looks like Pat Cummins is not leaving anything that is there to be won as captain. WTC, the 50-over Cricket World Cup and now the IPL final. A chance to end as the winner again. A great time personally for the man from New South Wales.

Sanju Samson | RR captain: It was a big game. I am really proud of the way we bowled in the first innings. We were found short of options in the middle overs against their spin, that's where we lost the game. It's very hard to guess actually when we are expecting some dew or when we are not. The wicket started behaving differently in the second innings, the ball started turning a bit, they used that advantage really well. They bowled their spin in the middle overs against our right-handed batsmen, that's where they were one-up against us. Against their left-arm spin, when the ball was stopping, we could have tried a bit more reverse-sweep or maybe use of the crease a bit more. They also bowled really well. We have had some brilliant games not only this season but from the last three years, it has been a great project for our franchise. We have found some really great talent for the country. Riyan Parag, Dhruv Jurel and a lot of them are looking really exciting not only for RR but definitely for the Indian cricket team. We have had some great seasons from the last three years. (On Sandeep Sharma) I am really happy for him. By not being picked in the auctions and coming back as a replacement. the way he bowled, he has definitely delivered. If we look at the numbers, Sandeep Sharma in the last two years, he will be the next guy after Bumrah. He has done a great job. (Final) The condition suits both of them, so let's see how they come back again in the powerplay. SRH batsmen are very interesting, they can definitely take the game away. KKR also will be confident, they look very exciting. It'll be a great game, that's what IPL has been giving us for the last 16 years.

Abhishek Sharma: To be honest I didn't know it would be this match (where I would bowl all 4 overs), but I was ready. I have been working on my bowling. I have been batting well in the last 2 years but it was my bowling that I had to work on and I did it with my dad. It (the pitch) was quicker when we were batting and it started to turn in the second innings, Patty used the spinners well. It was the pressure I have put in all the (practice) sessions that he (Cummins) gave me bowling today. We won the SMAT with Punjab and the momentum came from that, I was ready and worked hard. The message was simple - they gave us the freedom to go and express ourselves. It was one of my dreams to play in the IPL final and it is coming true.

Pat Cummins | SRH skipper: The boys have been fantastic all season. There's a great vibe in the squad as you can see and the final was the goal at the start of the season and we made it. We knew our strength was our batting and we wouldn't underestimate the experience we have in this squad, it's a dream having Bhuvi, Nattu and Unadkat, makes my job easy. [on whose decision it was to bring Shahbaz as impact player] Dan Vettori, left-arm orthodox and wanted as many left-arm orthodox as possible. [on Abhishek's bowling] That was a surprise, tried to stick one out of him with a couple of right-handers and he bowled beautifully and those two won it with their bowling in the middle overs. 170 was a tough chase and had we got a couple of wickets we knew we had a chance. I will never pretend to work out the pitch and conditions ever, different every week. It is for the whole franchise, probably 60 or 70 of them who put their heart and soul into this and hopefully one more left.

Shahbaz Ahmed | Player of the Match (translated from Hindi): The captain and coach told me depending on the situation we will use you, my role was to bat lower down the order and they said if we collapse we will send you. When I was batting, I felt that this wicket has something and the way Avesh and Sandeep bowled showed. I'm feeling proud at having got the Man of the Match in such a game, the atmosphere is quite relaxed in the camp. We will celebrate only after winning the final, tonight we will just relax.
